Excellent! Now I have gathered all the information. Let me create a comprehensive report for you.

## Exploration Complete: apps/web Directory Analysis

I've thoroughly explored the T3 Code monorepo's web application. Here's a comprehensive report:

---

## 1. OVERALL DIRECTORY STRUCTURE

**Key Directories:**
- `src/` - Main application source code
- `src/components/` - React components (UI + feature components)
- `src/components/ui/` - shadcn/ui component library
- `src/hooks/` - Custom React hooks
- `src/lib/` - Utility and library functions
- `src/routes/` - TanStack Router route definitions
- Root level: Vite, TypeScript, and build configs

**Complete src/ file listing:**
The application has 80+ non-test TypeScript/TSX files organized into:
- Core app files: `main.tsx`, `router.ts`, `store.ts`, `types.ts`
- State management: `store.ts`, `composerDraftStore.ts`, `terminalStateStore.ts`
- Route definitions: `__root.tsx`, `_chat.tsx`, `_chat.index.tsx`, `_chat.settings.tsx`
- Components: 40+ UI + feature components
- Libraries: 15+ utility/library modules
- Workers & APIs: WebSocket transport, native API integration, diff rendering

---

## 2. MAIN ENTRY POINTS - FULL CONTENTS

### **index.html**
```html
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="48x48" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,300..800;1,9..40,300..800&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <title>T3 Code (Alpha)</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="root"></div>
    <script type="module" src="/src/main.tsx"></script>
  </body>
</html>
```

### **src/main.tsx**
```typescript
import React from "react";
import ReactDOM from "react-dom/client";
import { RouterProvider } from "@tanstack/react-router";
import { createHashHistory, createBrowserHistory } from "@tanstack/react-router";

import "@xterm/xterm/css/xterm.css";
import "./index.css";

import { isElectron } from "./env";
import { getRouter } from "./router";
import { APP_DISPLAY_NAME } from "./branding";

const history = isElectron ? createHashHistory() : createBrowserHistory();

const router = getRouter(history);

document.title = APP_DISPLAY_NAME;

ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root") as HTMLElement).render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <RouterProvider router={router} />
  </React.StrictMode>,
);
```

**Key Notes:**
- Uses TanStack Router for routing (hash history for Electron, browser history for web)
- Imports global xterm CSS and index.css (Tailwind)
- Renders into `#root` div

---

## 3. REACT CONTEXT/PROVIDERS SETUP

The app uses **Zustand** for state management instead of React Context. Here's the complete provider chain:

### **Router-Level Providers** (`src/router.ts`)
```typescript
export function getRouter(history: RouterHistory) {
  const queryClient = new QueryClient();

  return createRouter({
    routeTree,
    history,
    context: {
      queryClient,
    },
    Wrap: ({ children }) =>
      createElement(
        QueryClientProvider,
        { client: queryClient },
        createElement(StoreProvider, null, children),
      ),
  });
}
```

**Provider stack (top to bottom):**
1. **QueryClientProvider** (@tanstack/react-query) - API caching & async state
2. **StoreProvider** - Custom Zustand provider wrapper
3. **RouterProvider** - TanStack Router

### **Root Route Providers** (`src/routes/__root.tsx`)
```typescript
function RootRouteView() {
  return (
    <ToastProvider>
      <AnchoredToastProvider>
        <EventRouter />
        <DesktopProjectBootstrap />
        <Outlet />
      </AnchoredToastProvider>
    </ToastProvider>
  );
}
```

**Additional providers:**
- **ToastProvider** & **AnchoredToastProvider** - Notification system
- **EventRouter** - Event subscription handler (lifecycle component)
- **DesktopProjectBootstrap** - Desktop-specific initialization

### **Feature-Specific Providers**

#### Chat Layout (`src/routes/_chat.tsx`)
```typescript
<SidebarProvider defaultOpen>
  <Sidebar side="left" collapsible="offcanvas">
    <ThreadSidebar />
  </Sidebar>
  <DiffWorkerPoolProvider>
    <Outlet />
  </DiffWorkerPoolProvider>
</SidebarProvider>
```

#### Diff Rendering (`src/components/DiffWorkerPoolProvider.tsx`)
```typescript
<WorkerPoolContextProvider
  poolOptions={{
    workerFactory: () => new DiffsWorker(),
    poolSize: workerPoolSize,
    totalASTLRUCacheSize: 240,
  }}
  highlighterOptions={{
    theme: diffThemeName,
    tokenizeMaxLineLength: 1_000,
  }}
>
  <DiffWorkerThemeSync themeName={diffThemeName} />
  {children}
</WorkerPoolContextProvider>
```

### **State Management Store** (`src/store.ts`)
Uses **Zustand** with localStorage persistence:

```typescript
export const useStore = create<AppStore>((set) => ({
  ...readPersistedState(),
  syncServerReadModel: (readModel) => set((state) => syncServerReadModel(state, readModel)),
  markThreadVisited: (threadId, visitedAt) =>
    set((state) => markThreadVisited(state, threadId, visitedAt)),
  // ... other actions
}));

export function StoreProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  useEffect(() => {
    persistState(useStore.getState());
  }, []);
  return createElement(Fragment, null, children);
}
```

**Store state shape:**
```typescript
interface AppState {
  projects: Project[];
  threads: Thread[];
  threadsHydrated: boolean;
}
```

**Persistence:**
- Key: `"t3code:renderer-state:v8"`
- Stores: `expandedProjectCwds` (expanded project folders)
- Cleans up legacy keys on every persist

---

## 4. THEMING & CSS CUSTOM PROPERTIES

### **src/index.css** - Complete Theming Implementation

**Tailwind + CSS Custom Properties Pattern:**

1. **Light Theme (root)**
```css
:root {
  color-scheme: light;
  --radius: 0.625rem;
  --background: var(--color-white);
  --foreground: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --primary: oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --primary-foreground: var(--color-white);
  --secondary: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --muted: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 4%);
  --border: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 8%);
  --input: --alpha(var(--color-black) / 10%);
  --ring: oklch(0.488 0.217 264);
  --destructive: var(--color-red-500);
  --info: var(--color-blue-500);
  --success: var(--color-emerald-500);
  --warning: var(--color-amber-500);
  /* ... 20+ CSS variables */
}
```

2. **Dark Theme (nested under .dark class)**
```css
@variant dark {
  color-scheme: dark;
  --background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 95%, var(--color-white));
  --foreground: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --primary: oklch(0.588 0.217 264);
  /* ... theme overrides */
}
```

3. **Radius Variants**
```css
--radius-sm: calc(var(--radius) - 4px);
--radius-md: calc(var(--radius) - 2px);
--radius-lg: var(--radius);
--radius-xl: calc(var(--radius) + 4px);
```

4. **Transition Suppression**
```css
.no-transitions,
.no-transitions *,
.no-transitions *::before,
.no-transitions *::after {
  transition-duration: 0s !important;
  animation-duration: 0s !important;
}
```

### **useTheme Hook** (`src/hooks/useTheme.ts`)

Custom hook with `useSyncExternalStore` pattern for theme management:

```typescript
export function useTheme() {
  const snapshot = useSyncExternalStore(subscribe, getSnapshot);
  const theme = snapshot.theme;

  const resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark" =
    theme === "system" ? (snapshot.systemDark ? "dark" : "light") : theme;

  const setTheme = useCallback((next: Theme) => {
    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, next);
    applyTheme(next, true);
    emitChange();
  }, []);

  return { theme, setTheme, resolvedTheme } as const;
}
```

**Features:**
- Stores theme preference in localStorage (`"t3code:theme"`)
- Syncs across browser tabs via storage events
- Respects system dark mode preference
- Prevents flash on page load with synchronous theme application
- Removes `no-transitions` class after applying theme changes

---

## 5. APP STRUCTURE - ROUTING & LAYOUTS

### **File Structure:**
```
src/routes/
├── __root.tsx          (Root layout with ToastProviders)
├── _chat.tsx           (Main chat layout with sidebar)
├── _chat.index.tsx     (Chat index/empty state)
└── _chat.settings.tsx  (Settings page)
```

### **Route Hierarchy:**
```
/ (__root)
└── / (_chat) [SidebarProvider + DiffWorkerPoolProvider]
    ├── / (index)
    └── /settings
```

### **Root Route** (`__root.tsx`)
- Error boundary with detailed error display
- Toast notification system (anchored & floating)
- Event subscription for server updates
- Desktop project bootstrap
- Server config watchers (keybindings, updates)

### **Chat Route Layout** (`_chat.tsx`)
- **Sidebar Provider** - Manages sidebar state (open/closed)
- **Thread Sidebar** - Left navigation with projects/threads
