# Custom Theme System — Implementation Plan

## Context

T3 Code has a basic `light | dark | system` mode toggle (in `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`) that controls a `.dark` CSS class on `<html>`. The task extends this with a **named color-theme system** (t3-dark, t3-light, t3-midnight) that carries full color/font metadata and writes resolved CSS custom-property values directly to `document.documentElement.style`, overriding the stylesheet. This lets future themes vary any design token (sidebar color, editor background, etc.) without touching CSS files.

The new system coexists with the existing `useTheme` light/dark toggle. The custom theme also manages the `.dark` class (last writer wins at runtime; on load the custom-theme module runs after `useTheme`).

---

## Files to Create

| # | Path | Purpose |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | `packages/shared/src/themes.ts` | Pure data: types, built-in themes, `getTheme`, `listThemes` |
| 2 | `apps/web/src/hooks/useCustomTheme.ts` | `useSyncExternalStore` hook for theme state + DOM application |
| 3 | `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` | Radio-group UI with color-swatch previews |

## Files to Modify

| # | Path | Change |
|---|------|--------|
| 4 | `packages/shared/package.json` | Add `"./themes"` subpath export |
| 5 | `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` | Add ThemeSelector sub-section inside Appearance |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `packages/shared/src/themes.ts`

Pure TypeScript, no browser or Node.js APIs (safe for both environments).

```ts
export interface ThemeColors {
  background: string;   // resolved CSS color (hex/oklch/rgb — no var())
  foreground: string;
  accent: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface Theme {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  colors: ThemeColors;
  fontFamily: string;
  fontSize: string;     // e.g. "14px"
}
```

Define **three named constants** to avoid `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` issues, then compose the array:

```ts
const T3_DARK: Theme = {
  id: "t3-dark",
  name: "T3 Dark",
  colors: {
    background: "oklch(0.095 0 0)",        // ≈ neutral-950 (matches existing dark CSS)
    foreground: "oklch(0.963 0 0)",        // neutral-100
    accent:     "rgba(255,255,255,0.04)",
    sidebar:    "oklch(0.085 0 0)",
    editor:     "oklch(0.09 0 0)",
    terminal:   "oklch(0.07 0 0)",
    statusBar:  "oklch(0.075 0 0)",
  },
  fontFamily: '"DM Sans",-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,"Segoe UI",system-ui,sans-serif',
  fontSize:   "14px",
};

const T3_LIGHT: Theme = {
  id: "t3-light",
  name: "T3 Light",
  colors: {
    background: "oklch(1 0 0)",            // white
    foreground: "oklch(0.368 0 0)",        // neutral-800
    accent:     "rgba(0,0,0,0.04)",
    sidebar:    "oklch(0.97 0 0)",
    editor:     "oklch(1 0 0)",
    terminal:   "oklch(0.08 0 0)",
    statusBar:  "oklch(0.93 0 0)",
  },
  fontFamily: '"DM Sans",-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,"Segoe UI",system-ui,sans-serif',
  fontSize:   "14px",
};

const T3_MIDNIGHT: Theme = {
  id: "t3-midnight",
  name: "T3 Midnight",
  colors: {
    background: "oklch(0.07 0.02 264)",    // dark blue-tinted
    foreground: "oklch(0.93 0 0)",
    accent:     "rgba(99,102,241,0.12)",   // indigo tint
    sidebar:    "oklch(0.06 0.02 264)",
    editor:     "oklch(0.08 0.015 264)",
    terminal:   "oklch(0.05 0 0)",
    statusBar:  "oklch(0.055 0.02 264)",
  },
  fontFamily: '"DM Sans",-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,"Segoe UI",system-ui,sans-serif',
  fontSize:   "14px",
};

export const DEFAULT_THEME: Theme = T3_DARK;
export const DEFAULT_THEME_ID = T3_DARK.id;

export const BUILT_IN_THEMES: ReadonlyArray<Theme> = [T3_DARK, T3_LIGHT, T3_MIDNIGHT];

export function listThemes(): ReadonlyArray<Theme> {
  return BUILT_IN_THEMES;
}

export function getTheme(id: string): Theme | undefined {
  return BUILT_IN_THEMES.find((t) => t.id === id);
}
```

### Step 2 — `packages/shared/package.json` (add subpath export)

Mirror the pattern of existing entries:

```json
"./themes": {
  "types": "./src/themes.ts",
  "import": "./src/themes.ts"
}
```

### Step 3 — `apps/web/src/hooks/useCustomTheme.ts`

Follows the exact module-level `useSyncExternalStore` pattern from the existing `useTheme.ts` (module-level listeners array, `emitChange`, `getSnapshot` with stable object caching, `subscribe` with storage-event listener, immediate `applyTheme` call on module load).

Key implementation details:
- **Storage key**: `"t3code:custom-theme"` (distinct from `"t3code:theme"`)
- **`applyTheme(themeId, suppressTransitions?)`**:
  - Looks up theme with `getTheme(themeId) ?? DEFAULT_THEME`
  - Uses `document.documentElement.classList.add("no-transitions")` and reflow trick (same as `useTheme.ts`)
  - Sets these CSS custom properties via `style.setProperty()` (overrides stylesheet values):
    - `--background` ← `theme.colors.background`
    - `--foreground` ← `theme.colors.foreground`
    - `--card` ← `theme.colors.background`
    - `--card-foreground` ← `theme.colors.foreground`
    - `--popover` ← `theme.colors.background`
    - `--popover-foreground` ← `theme.colors.foreground`
    - `--accent` ← `theme.colors.accent`
    - `--accent-foreground` ← `theme.colors.foreground`
    - `--muted` ← `theme.colors.accent`
    - `--t3-sidebar` ← `theme.colors.sidebar` (new custom var, for future use)
    - `--t3-editor` ← `theme.colors.editor`
    - `--t3-terminal` ← `theme.colors.terminal`
    - `--t3-status-bar` ← `theme.colors.statusBar`
  - Sets `font-family` and `font-size` on `document.body.style` from `theme.fontFamily/fontSize`
  - Toggles `.dark` class: `id !== "t3-light"` → dark
- **`getSnapshot()`**: returns cached theme ID string (stable ref when unchanged)
- **`subscribe()`**: listens to `StorageEvent` for the custom-theme key (cross-tab sync)
- **Hook export**: `useCustomTheme()` returns `{ theme: Theme, setTheme(id: string): void, availableThemes: ReadonlyArray<Theme> }`
- `setTheme` calls `localStorage.setItem`, `applyTheme(id, true)`, `emitChange()`
- `useEffect` keeps DOM in sync on mount/re-render (same pattern as `useTheme.ts`)

### Step 4 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx`

Reuses the exact same radio-button styling pattern from the Appearance section in `_chat.settings.tsx` (border, `bg-primary/8`, `border-primary/60` for selected; `hover:bg-accent` for unselected; "Selected" badge).

Adds a **color-swatch row** (3 small rounded circles, `background` / `foreground` / `accent` colors) using inline `style={{ backgroundColor: ... }}` so previews work regardless of the active theme.

```tsx
import { useCustomTheme } from "~/hooks/useCustomTheme";

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { theme, setTheme, availableThemes } = useCustomTheme();
  return (
    <div className="space-y-2" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Color theme">
      {availableThemes.map((t) => {
        const selected = theme.id === t.id;
        return (
          <button
            key={t.id}
            type="button"
            role="radio"
            aria-checked={selected}
            className={/* same pattern as existing THEME_OPTIONS buttons */}
            onClick={() => setTheme(t.id)}
          >
            {/* swatch: 3 circles */}
            <div className="flex shrink-0 gap-1">
              <span className="block h-4 w-4 rounded-full border border-black/10"
                style={{ backgroundColor: t.colors.background }} />
              <span className="block h-4 w-4 rounded-full border border-black/10"
                style={{ backgroundColor: t.colors.foreground }} />
              <span className="block h-4 w-4 rounded-full border border-black/10"
                style={{ backgroundColor: t.colors.accent === "rgba..." ? "#888" : t.colors.accent }} />
            </div>
            <span className="flex-1 text-sm font-medium">{t.name}</span>
            {selected && <span className="... text-primary">Active</span>}
          </button>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

> Note: The accent swatch uses a solid fallback color for rgba values — or the swatch can be rendered with `background: t.colors.accent` directly and rely on the checkerboard pattern showing through.

### Step 5 — `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` (wire in)

Inside the existing `"Appearance"` `<section>`, after the light/dark/system radio group and the "Active theme" line, add a visual separator and a "Color Theme" sub-section:

```tsx
import { ThemeSelector } from "../components/ThemeSelector";

// After the existing theme radio group inside the Appearance section:
<div className="mt-5 border-t border-border pt-4">
  <h3 className="mb-1 text-xs font-medium text-foreground">Color Theme</h3>
  <p className="mb-3 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
    Choose a built-in color theme for the editor.
  </p>
  <ThemeSelector />
</div>
```

No new imports from `useCustomTheme` are needed in the settings route itself — `ThemeSelector` encapsulates the hook call.

---

## TypeScript Strictness Checklist

- `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`: avoided by exporting `DEFAULT_THEME` as a named constant; hook uses `getTheme(id) ?? DEFAULT_THEME` (both `Theme`, never `undefined`)
- `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`: all `ThemeColors` and `Theme` fields are required (no optional)
- `strict`: `getTheme` returns `Theme | undefined`; every call-site handles the `undefined` case

---

## Verification

1. **TypeCheck**: `bun typecheck` from repo root (or `packages/shared` and `apps/web` individually)
2. **Lint**: `bun lint`
3. **Manual**:
   - Navigate to Settings → Appearance section
   - Confirm three color-theme options appear with swatches
   - Selecting "T3 Light" should switch the UI to light palette, update localStorage `t3code:custom-theme`
   - Selecting "T3 Midnight" should switch to dark blue-tinted palette
   - Reload page — chosen theme should persist (applied before first paint)
   - Open a second tab — theme change in one tab syncs to the other (StorageEvent listener)

